Found the issue! Looking at your CSS, I can see the problem is with how .tab-panel is styled. The issue is in these rules:

```css
.tab-panel {
    display: none;
    animation: fadeIn 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.25, 1);
}

.tab-panel.active {
    display: block;
}
```

The problem is that display: none completely removes the element from the rendering flow. When you try to animate it with fadeIn, it can't properly transition because you can't animate from display: none to display: block.

Here's the fixed CSS for the tab panels:

```css
/* Tab Panels - FIXED */
.tab-panel {
    opacity: 0;
    height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    visibility: hidden;
    animation: fadeIn 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.25, 1);
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease, height 0.3s ease;
}

.tab-panel.active {
    opacity: 1;
    height: auto;
    overflow: visible;
    visibility: visible;
    display: block;
}

@keyframes fadeIn {
    from { 
        opacity: 0; 
        transform: translateY(15px); 
    }
    to { 
        opacity: 1; 
        transform: translateY(0); 
    }
}
```

And update your JavaScript switchTab() method to use this approach:

```javascript
// Switch between tabs - FIXED VERSION
switchTab(tabName) {
    console.log(`Switching to tab: ${tabName}`);
    
    // Update tab buttons
    document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn').forEach(btn => {
        const isActive = btn.dataset.tab === tabName;
        btn.classList.toggle('active', isActive);
        btn.setAttribute('aria-selected', isActive);
    });

    // Update tab panels - Use opacity/height instead of display
    document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {
        const isActive = panel.id === `${tabName}-panel`;
        
        if (isActive) {
            panel.classList.add('active');
            panel.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
            panel.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'false');
            
            // Force reflow to trigger animation
            void panel.offsetWidth;
        } else {
            panel.classList.remove('active');
            panel.setAttribute('tabindex', '-1');
            panel.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');
        }
    });

    // Hide export download and progress
    const exportDownload = document.getElementById('export-download');
    const pdfProgress = document.getElementById('pdf-progress');
    
    if (exportDownload) exportDownload.style.display = 'none';
    if (pdfProgress) pdfProgress.style.display = 'none';
    
    // Hide previews when switching away from export
    if (tabName !== 'export') {
        this.hideCSVPreview();
        this.hideJSONPreview();
    }
    
    // Render logbook if switching to that tab
    if (tabName === 'logbook') {
        this.renderLogbook();
    }
    
    // Scroll to top on mobile
    if (window.innerWidth < 768) {
        window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
    }
    
    // Focus the active tab panel for accessibility
    const tabPanel = document.getElementById(`${tabName}-panel`);
    if (tabPanel) {
        setTimeout(() => {
            tabPanel.focus();
        }, 350); // Wait for animation to complete
    }
    
    // Debug log
    console.log(`Active tab: ${tabName}, Panel visibility: ${tabPanel ? 'found' : 'not found'}`);
}
```

If you want to keep using display: none/display: block instead of opacity, here's an alternative fix using JavaScript to handle the transition:

```javascript
// Switch between tabs - ALTERNATIVE FIX using display property
switchTab(tabName) {
    console.log(`Switching to tab: ${tabName}`);
    
    // Update tab buttons
    document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn').forEach(btn => {
        const isActive = btn.dataset.tab === tabName;
        btn.classList.toggle('active', isActive);
        btn.setAttribute('aria-selected', isActive);
    });

    // Update tab panels - Use setTimeout for animation
    document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {
        const isActive = panel.id === `${tabName}-panel`;
        
        if (isActive) {
            // First make it visible with opacity 0
            panel.style.opacity = '0';
            panel.style.display = 'block';
            panel.classList.add('active');
            panel.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
            
            // Then fade in
            setTimeout(() => {
                panel.style.transition = 'opacity 0.3s ease';
                panel.style.opacity = '1';
            }, 10);
        } else {
            // Fade out then hide
            if (panel.classList.contains('active')) {
                panel.style.opacity = '0';
                setTimeout(() => {
                    panel.style.display = 'none';
                    panel.classList.remove('active');
                }, 300);
            } else {
                panel.style.display = 'none';
                panel.classList.remove('active');
            }
            panel.setAttribute('tabindex', '-1');
        }
    });

    // ... rest of the method remains the same
}
```

And update the CSS slightly:

```css
.tab-panel {
    display: none;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
}

.tab-panel.active {
    /* display: block is set by JavaScript */
    opacity: 1;
}
```

The key issue is that display: none can't be animated, so you need to use either:

1. Opacity/height approach: Use opacity: 0, height: 0, visibility: hidden instead of display: none
2. JavaScript-controlled approach: Use JavaScript to handle the fade in/out before changing display property

I recommend the first approach (opacity/height) as it's more performant and easier to maintain.
